  "local_port": 38138,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I wear to prom?",
  "response": "Choosing an outfit for prom can be exciting! Here are some tips to help you decide what to wear:\n\n### For Guys:\n1. **Suit or Tuxedo**: A classic choice. Black or navy are popular colors, but feel free to choose a color that suits your style.\n2. **Shirt**: A white or light-colored dress shirt is standard. Consider the neckline of your date's dress if you're matching outfits.\n3. **Tie or Bow Tie**: Match the color to your date's dress or go for a classic black.\n4. **Shoes**: Dress shoes in black or brown. Make sure they're comfortable for dancing.\n5. **Accessories**: A pocket square, cufflinks, or a watch can add a personal touch.\n\n### For Girls:\n1. **Dress**: Choose a style that makes you feel confident. Popular options include:\n   - **Ball Gowns**: Full skirt, often floor-length.\n   - **Mermaid/Trumpet**: Fitted to the knees, then flares out.\n   - **A-Line**: Fitted at the hips, then gradually widens.\n   - **Sheath**: Straight and narrow, often more modern.\n2. **Color**: Pick a color that complements your skin tone. Don't be afraid to go bold or stick to classics like black, red, or navy.\n3. **Shoes**: Heels are traditional, but comfort is key. Consider flats or wedges if you prefer.\n4. **Accessories**: Jewelry, a clutch, and perhaps a wrap or shawl. Keep it simple to let your dress shine.\n5. **Hair and Makeup**: Decide if you want an updo, down, or half-up style. Makeup can be natural or glam, depending on your preference.\n\n### General Tips:\n- **Comfort**: Make sure you can move and dance comfortably in your outfit.\n- **Weather**: Consider the season and venue when choosing your outfit.\n- **Theme**: If your prom has a theme, you might want to incorporate it into your outfit.\n- **Budget**: Set a budget and look for options within it. Renting a tux or buying a secondhand dress can be cost-effective.\n\nRemember, prom is about celebrating, so choose an outfit that makes you feel fantastic and reflects your personal style!",
